Comment: 0,0:01:50.55,0:01:59.52,Title,,0,0,0,,Steer for the Clouds! \NCapture the South Bird!
Comment: 0,0:23:31.56,0:23:35.52,Title,,0,0,0,,Dreams Don't Come True?! \NBellamy versus the Saruyama Alliance
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,OPENING
Comment: 0,0:21:54.54,0:21:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,ENDING
Dialogue: 10,0:02:01.43,0:02:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you need to tell us, old guy?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:03.94,0:02:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Here. I'll start by telling you everything I know about the sky island.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:10.11,0:02:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,None of it's certain, but it's up to you \Nif you wanna believe it or not!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:14.76,0:02:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! We believe you!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:16.03,0:02:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Geez, you're fast!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:16.95,0:02:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a strange phenomenon \Nthat occurs in these waters...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:20.95,0:02:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes it'll turn to night, \Neven though it's the middle of the day.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:25.54,0:02:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! We saw that! Right?!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:28.50,0:02:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! \NNight came, and then some monsters appeared!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:34.88,0:02:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The giants?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:36.39,0:02:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a story about where they \Ncome from, but forget 'em for now.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:40.72,0:02:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This sudden nightfall...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:46.40,0:02:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's caused by the shadows \Nof extremely compact clouds...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:49.73,0:02:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean cumulonimbus clouds? \NBut it was too dark to be clouds...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:54.48,0:02:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! You're so dumb, old guy!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:56.82,0:02:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets cloudy on days \Nwhen there's lots of clouds!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:59.03,0:03:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Cloudy!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:00.45,0:03:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Cloudy!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:01.04,0:03:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up and listen!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:03.38,0:03:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There are clouds known as "cumuloregalis clouds."
Dialogue: 10,0:03:06.83,0:03:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They pile high into the sky but \Nproduce no air currents or rain.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:12.38,0:03:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,When they appear high in the sky, \Neven sunlight is blocked out,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:17.84,0:03:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,bringing afternoon "nighttime" to the ground.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:20.47,0:03:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,One theory has it that cumuloregalis \Nclouds are fossilized clouds
Dialogue: 10,0:03:24.06,0:03:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that have floated in the sky for \Nthousands and thousands of years.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:28.48,0:03:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's ridiculous! Clouds with no air currents even after building up?!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:33.28,0:03:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You're free to believe they can't exist.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:35.90,0:03:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not asking you to believe me!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:38.78,0:03:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They're mystery clouds, then?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:40.99,0:03:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty much. \NThere's still no explanation for them.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:44.08,0:03:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You're awesome, Luffy!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:45.50,0:03:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen. If a sky island really does exist...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:49.76,0:03:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,...that'd be the only possible place!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:51.46,0:03:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! Gotcha! Let's go above those clouds!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:54.63,0:03:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Get up, Zoro!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:55.80,0:03:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Is it morning?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:56.84,0:03:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Get ready, everyone! Cloud rudder full!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:59.84,0:04:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for filling us in, old guy!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:03.11,0:04:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,How many times do I gotta say \Nwe don't know how to get there?!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:07.52,0:04:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now comes the real problem.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:08.90,0:04:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me start by saying this... \NPut your lives on the line!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:10.86,0:04:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We're already near death...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:12.66,0:04:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The Knock-Up Stream is a \Ncurrent that shoots into the air...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:16.65,0:04:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You can theoretically take it into the sky. \NUnderstand?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:20.66,0:04:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a current that can send ships flying, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:24.62,0:04:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! \NThen it just needs to send us above the clouds!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:28.41,0:04:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yahoo!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:31.42,0:04:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,On a current?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:32.63,0:04:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But wouldn't we just end up \Nsmashing back into the ocean?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:37.05,0:04:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Normally, yeah. The key is timing.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:40.59,0:04:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's easy to talk about being sent up the current,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:46.10,0:04:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's not gonna be as nice \Na trip as you guys think.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:52.27,0:04:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The Knock-Up Stream is a natural disaster.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:55.69,0:04:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's something that should normally be avoided!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:00.40,0:05:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How exactly does a water \Ncurrent rise into the sky?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:03.78,0:05:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We've never heard of anything like that before...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:08.25,0:05:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:11.25,0:05:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, we can only guess as to \Nhow that monstrous current works.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:16.46,0:05:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,No one's dumb enough to \Njump in and find out, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:20.42,0:05:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The accepted theory goes like this!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:26.01,0:05:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Deep beneath the sea floor, \Nthere are large cavities,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:29.48,0:05:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and low-temperature sea water seeps into them.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:32.75,0:05:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The heat from the earth below \Nturns that water into steam,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:36.52,0:05:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and the resulting pressure causes \Nan explosion on the sea floor.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:39.77,0:05:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,One big enough to send the sea flying \Nand create a current into the sky!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:48.54,0:05:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,For about one minute, the sea \Ncontinues to rise into the sky.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:53.12,0:05:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,One minute?! What size of explosion are we talking about here?!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:57.84,0:06:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The explosions change location each time,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:00.38,0:06:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and occur five times a month.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:02.80,0:06:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You want us to be blown into smithereens...?!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:06.05,0:06:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But, y'know,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:07.85,0:06:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,describing a grand natural phenomenon \Nwith words and logic is foolish.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:12.73,0:06:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,S-So, basically, we gotta ride this current \Nthat only appears five times a month
Dialogue: 10,0:06:18.98,0:06:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and hope the sky island shows up?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:21.07,0:06:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. And if you miss, you'll fall \Nback down, slam into the ocean...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:29.83,0:06:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,...and then you'll all end up at the bottom of the sea.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:34.08,0:06:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,A-Alright! Let's give up on the sky island!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:39.25,0:06:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's impossible!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:41.26,0:06:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You gotta have the luckiest luck \Nthat's ever lucked to make it there!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:48.93,0:06:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be fine! Let's go!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:51.06,0:06:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,How did I know?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:52.14,0:06:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,"We'll be fine"? How can you say \Nsuch groundless stuff so easily...?!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:56.27,0:06:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, just look at the Going Merry now!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:59.15,0:07:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks so pitiful!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:01.69,0:07:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't stand up to a gigantic disaster like that!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:05.57,0:07:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true. Even in mint condition, \Nthat ship wouldn't stand a chance.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:10.17,0:07:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:11.29,0:07:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Speed, weight, strength...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:13.58,0:07:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That boat'd be blasted apart in the explosion.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:17.63,0:07:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But... See! It really is impossible!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:21.75,0:07:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But don't you worry about that.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.47,0:07:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have Masira and Shojo help take you there.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:27.89,0:07:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Only after we strengthen your ship, of course.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:30.98,0:07:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Just leave it to us!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:33.47,0:07:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, guys!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:34.96,0:07:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Didn't even ask us...{\i0}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:38.48,0:07:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you even understand?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:40.52,0:07:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Understand what?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:41.15,0:07:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,For starters... Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:43.19,0:07:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The most we can stay on \Nthis island is one more day!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:47.86,0:07:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, the Log Pose will \Nstart pointing to the next island!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:52.33,0:07:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Yeah! We won't make it in time!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:55.62,0:07:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously, old man! You're not a psychic!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:58.21,0:08:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I doubt you know, but how many days will it be
Dialogue: 10,0:08:00.50,0:08:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,until the Knock-Up Stream and \Nthe cumuloregalis clouds line up?!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.44,0:08:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no! How many months?! \NNo, how many years?!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:10.47,0:08:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow afternoon. \NIf you're going, you better get ready!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:13.68,0:08:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't make it in that time!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:15.81,0:08:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? If you don't like it, then just quit!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:20.98,0:08:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-You're lying!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.61,0:08:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't right! We just met you today! \NAren't you being {\i1}too{\i0} nice?!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:27.82,0:08:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus...!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:29.91,0:08:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on, Usopp!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:31.07,0:08:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up, you!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:32.83,0:08:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow just {\i1}happens{\i0} to be the perfect chance
Dialogue: 10,0:08:35.62,0:08:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to go to this legendary, unknown "sky island"?!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:40.10,0:08:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll help strengthen \Nour ship and take us there?!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:44.46,0:08:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's way too convenient!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:45.96,0:08:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What exactly are you scheming?!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:48.38,0:08:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus you're Noland the Liar's descendant! \NWe can't trust you!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:56.60,0:09:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Old-timer! Dinner's ready!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:00.02,0:09:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Move!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:01.12,0:09:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Nami-{\i1}san{\i0}! Dinner's...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:06.28,0:09:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,W-What?! Are you gonna fight?!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:09.36,0:09:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever "midday night" \Nis confirmed in Masira's turf,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:12.70,0:09:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,cumuloregalis clouds appear in \Nthe southern skies the next day.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:18.29,0:09:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And judging from its five-per-month rate,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:20.62,0:09:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the Knock-Up Stream will \Nprobably be active tomorrow.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:25.17,0:09:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll happen somewhere south of here.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:28.17,0:09:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a 100% certainty, but there's \Na good chance it'll be tomorrow!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:39.68,0:09:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad to have met fools like you.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:45.98,0:09:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's go and have some food! \NTake it easy at my place today...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:51.11,0:09:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,...comrades!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:56.08,0:09:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Food! Hurry, Usopp!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:58.12,0:09:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! C'mon!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:59.33,0:10:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Chopper! Go get Robin-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:01.08,0:10:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.13,0:10:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like all we can do is try \Nour best to get into the sky...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:08.63,0:10:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Though in the end, it's up to luck...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:10.89,0:10:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Nami. Am I miserable and cowardly?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:14.35,0:10:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You forgot "stupid."
Dialogue: 10,0:10:16.31,0:10:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I know how you feel. Now go apologize.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:22.27,0:10:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, old guy!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:24.98,0:10:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What the...?! Yuck! Don't wipe your snot on me!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:34.78,0:10:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Today's booze is especially great!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:38.03,0:10:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Eat up, eat up! \NThe saury full course is just getting started!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:41.58,0:10:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:43.12,0:10:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotcha, salvage bum! \NThat's a Tabasco Bomber!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:46.54,0:10:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, you! Long-nose!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:50.38,0:10:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Girlie! Come sit here!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:52.51,0:10:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's 100 years too early to \Nhave Nami-{\i1}san{\i0} wait on you!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:04.77,0:11:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,"I saw gold...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:08.02,0:11:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,...in the skull's right eye!"
Dialogue: 10,0:11:09.73,0:11:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Gold?!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:14.07,0:11:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That tear-soaked sentence was \Nthe last thing Noland wrote.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:19.45,0:11:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,"I saw gold in the skull's right eye..."
Dialogue: 10,0:11:23.37,0:11:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Noland was executed that same day.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:26.41,0:11:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Even after coming to Jaya, \Nthose words make no sense at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:30.42,0:11:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,"The skull's right eye..."
Dialogue: 10,0:11:32.30,0:11:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it referring to the name \Nof a city that once existed?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:35.76,0:11:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Or was it an allusion to his own death?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:38.34,0:11:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The blank pages that follow say nothing...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:42.43,0:11:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why we dive!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:44.48,0:11:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a dream! On the sea floor!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:48.02,0:11:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:51.77,0:11:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We're gonna fly!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:55.28,0:11:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Not if you keep eating like that, we won't!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:02.28,0:12:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's gotten quite late, but I see it, Bellamy.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:06.25,0:12:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare to go ashore.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:08.71,0:12:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Dream-chasing fools deserve \Nmore than a few lumps!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:28.60,0:12:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,"The day I arrived on Jaya. \NEntry for May 21, 1122."
Dialogue: 10,0:12:34.48,0:12:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Noland! Noland!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:36.74,0:12:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,"Upon landing on the island, \Nwe heard strange bird calls
Dialogue: 10,0:12:39.57,0:12:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and the sound of a very large \Nbell coming from the forest.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:46.29,0:12:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The sound from that huge \Ngold bell resonated far and wide,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:51.92,0:12:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,almost as if showing off the \Nprosperity of a city long past!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:56.96,0:13:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We thought we knew everything \Nafter living for a few decades..."
Dialogue: 10,0:13:02.34,0:13:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Noland! Noland!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:04.93,0:13:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,"...but experiencing the transience \Nof this civilization that flourished
Dialogue: 10,0:13:09.35,0:13:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,for a long time on the wide \Nopen sea left us speechless!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:12.66,0:13:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The sound of the bell had \Nus stopped in our tracks!"
Dialogue: 10,0:13:19.28,0:13:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Noland's so cool!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:22.28,0:13:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! A giant gold bell!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:25.24,0:13:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute, old guy! \NYou like Noland after all!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:30.87,0:13:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at this!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.00,0:13:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! Gold bells!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:34.71,0:13:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how exactly are those "giant"?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:38.09,0:13:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,These aren't that bell. \NThey're bell-shaped ingots.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:42.72,0:13:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We found these three on the sea floor.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:44.55,0:13:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Ingots?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:45.55,0:13:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! So there really is a city of gold!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:47.97,0:13:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't prove that.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:50.64,0:13:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You could find that much gold in any old ruins.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:54.90,0:13:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But it does prove that there \Nwas a civilization in this area.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:58.82,0:14:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Ingots are made to have standardized weights.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:02.82,0:14:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means they were used for trade.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:05.32,0:14:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. And the strange bird calls mentioned before that...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:09.33,0:14:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Masira!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.75,0:14:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! There's more?!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:14.21,0:14:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This one's huge!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:15.55,0:14:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all of 'em.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:16.54,0:14:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! It's so pretty!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.97,0:14:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Gold bells and a bird...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:20.92,0:14:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you suppose they were symbols of old Jaya?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:25.18,0:14:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Dunno, but I think they were \Npart of some sort of model.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:29.43,0:14:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This here's called a South Bird, \Nand they still exist on this island!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:33.98,0:14:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Do they have weird calls?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:36.27,0:14:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep. Just like the logbook says!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:38.33,0:14:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Sailors have long used South Birds to...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:45.11,0:14:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, crap!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:46.91,0:14:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?! What's wrong?!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:48.49,0:14:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This is bad! You guys! \NGo into the forest! The southern forest!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:52.33,0:14:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?! What're you talking about?! \NAre you crazy, old guy?!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:55.04,0:14:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Go catch this bird! Right now!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:57.88,0:14:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?! What for?!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:59.38,0:15:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we need a bird?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:00.71,0:15:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen closely! The Knock-Up Stream \Nyou're heading for tomorrow
Dialogue: 10,0:15:05.80,0:15:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is located directly south of this cape.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:08.89,0:15:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you going to get there?!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:11.09,0:15:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Just sail straight there, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:13.31,0:15:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Grand Line, you know!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:15.39,0:15:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you're on the open sea, \Nthere's no way to get your bearings!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:18.86,0:15:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:20.48,0:15:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We're heading for ocean, not an island, \Nso we have no guide to rely on!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:24.86,0:15:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how {\i1}do{\i0} we go straight south?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:28.16,0:15:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You use that bird's behavior!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:31.83,0:15:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Some types of animals have accurate, \Ninternal magnets
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.25,0:15:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,which allow them to get their bearings.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:38.71,0:15:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you're lower than an animal, Zoro!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:41.27,0:15:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Like you're anyone to talk!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.89,0:15:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,South Birds are the greatest of such animals!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:48.89,0:15:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how vast the land \Nor sea they're thrown into,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:52.14,0:15:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,their bodies will always indicate \Nthe direction accurately.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:57.73,0:16:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, without one of these birds, \Nyou're going nowhere!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:00.94,0:16:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't even get the \Nchance to go to the sky island!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.49,0:16:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:05.82,0:16:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you telling us this now?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:08.70,0:16:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Quit fussing!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:10.53,0:16:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no time! Hurry! Don't dilly-dally!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:14.04,0:16:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You want us to go into the forest \Nin the middle of the night?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:16.79,0:16:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You forgot these!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:20.04,0:16:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We're gonna get started on your beat-up ship!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:23.46,0:16:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that I think about it, \Nthere was no time to be partyin'!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:27.05,0:16:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, why are you telling us this now?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:28.97,0:16:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen! Make sure you catch at \Nleast one South Bird before dawn!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:35.81,0:16:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pitch dark!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:37.02,0:16:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Quit pulling me!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:39.85,0:16:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not my fault! \NMy hands are moving on their own!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:43.57,0:16:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,My stomach's so full... \NI don't think I can chase birds...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:48.49,0:16:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Where {\i1}are{\i0} these weird birds?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:51.32,0:16:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just catch one so we \Ncan get back to drinking!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:54.09,0:16:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How did we wind up doing this so suddenly?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.83,0:16:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,– You're in the way! \N– Man! Couldn't he have told us during the day?!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:01.38,0:17:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, where are the birds?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:02.67,0:17:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If we knew where they were, \Nwe wouldn't be out looking for 'em!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:06.39,0:17:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Our only clue is that they have a weird call...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:08.84,0:17:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And they look just like that gold statue...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:11.84,0:17:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there really such dumb-looking birds?!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:15.43,0:17:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus "weird call" is way too vague! \NHow're we supposed to know?!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:19.35,0:17:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He said we'd know once we're in the forest...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:25.61,0:17:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,A weird call!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:27.11,0:17:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:28.07,0:17:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:29.19,0:17:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point, we got no other choice!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:31.74,0:17:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We have three nets. \NLet's split into three groups and search!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:34.41,0:17:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:35.37,0:17:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go! Let's beat up those weird birds!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:39.71,0:17:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean catch!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:47.75,0:17:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry! Whatever we run into, \NI'll protect you, Nami-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:51.51,0:17:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Sanji-{\i1}kun{\i0}! What about me?!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:52.88,0:17:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Hell if I care! Quit being insecure!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:55.43,0:17:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, let's catch a bird \Nso we can get out of this forest!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:59.32,0:18:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's start by listening closely \Nfor that bird we heard earlier.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:05.69,0:18:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That bird call!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:06.94,0:18:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Jooo! Come out! Joooo!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:09.78,0:18:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:12.65,0:18:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What're you catching me for?!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:14.36,0:18:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Nami! That's a cool thing you got on! \NWhere'd you get it?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:17.62,0:18:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:22.58,0:18:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Spider!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:24.30,0:18:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? It's just a spider! \NYou poor thing... Come here!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:27.52,0:18:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiders are yucky, you moron! \NToss it away somewhere!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:31.38,0:18:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Get away, Usopp! I bet it's poisonous!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:35.18,0:18:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They're falling from the trees!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:37.19,0:18:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This is too gross!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:38.76,0:18:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's probably a species of tarantula!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:41.56,0:18:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's alright! They won't spit poison \Nas long as we don't do anything!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:45.44,0:18:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to fight spiders a long time ago!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:47.56,0:18:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you can count me out when \Nit comes to creepy bugs like that!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:51.78,0:18:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Same here! I totally hate them! \NTotally! Hurry and throw it far away!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:55.61,0:18:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? But those moths and \Ncentipedes don't bother you?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:08.92,0:19:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate moths and centipedes!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:11.51,0:19:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahh! Don't leave me behind!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:16.26,0:19:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear screams...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:17.72,0:19:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget about 'em.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:23.52,0:19:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,A centipede, huh? It's pretty damn big...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:26.44,0:19:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not nice to kill everything. Poor thing...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:30.23,0:19:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what it gets for trying to attack me.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:33.57,0:19:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:34.53,0:19:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:35.53,0:19:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the path we just took here.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:40.70,0:19:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That bird call... This way.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:44.25,0:19:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch out for that quagmire.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:48.04,0:19:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Wait for...!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:54.51,0:19:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotcha!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:55.76,0:19:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, Chopper! It's an Atlas!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:58.22,0:19:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Atlas?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:59.22,0:20:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yup! Atlases and Hercules are the most admired bugs in the world!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:04.22,0:20:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? Beetles?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:06.69,0:20:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You never heard of 'em?! \NThey're super hard to catch!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.56,0:20:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is better, them or the One Piece?!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:11.90,0:20:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm... That's hard!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:14.07,0:20:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Luffy! There's something here, too!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:16.65,0:20:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! It's a Miyama!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:19.19,0:20:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Catch it!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:21.74,0:20:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It flew away!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:23.33,0:20:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, you...!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:26.83,0:20:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,After it! Don't let it get away!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:30.71,0:20:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,A beehive! Run!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:46.22,0:20:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with this forest?!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:49.14,0:20:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Luffy! Look there!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:50.85,0:20:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that bird!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:51.86,0:20:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He{\i0} dropped the beehives!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:55.61,0:20:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:56.36,0:20:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Did he say something?!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:59.99,0:21:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, "I'll kill you for invading this forest!"
Dialogue: 10,0:21:14.75,0:21:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now, boy! Don't be making us mad!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:18.92,0:21:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not nice to suddenly show up \Nat night and demand gold, kiddos.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:23.80,0:21:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave! We got work to do now!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:29.10,0:21:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You're bodyguards, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:30.98,0:21:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, there {\i1}was{\i0} \Na pirate named Cricket...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:34.45,0:21:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard the sad tale of your \NMontblanc family at the pub.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:38.24,0:21:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It moved me so.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:40.15,0:21:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Treasure someone else struggled to \Nget has a special flavor all its own!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:45.87,0:21:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanna know what people call me?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:49.50,0:21:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The Hyena!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:10.54,0:23:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Old guy! We caught a bird!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:12.54,0:23:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,W-What happened, old diamond-head?!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:14.04,0:23:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Sorry!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:16.83,0:23:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing we could do! We're pathetic!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:19.04,0:23:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The gold's been stolen!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:21.00,0:23:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's alright! Forget about that junk!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:23.47,0:23:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Bellamy's mark!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:24.97,0:23:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be back by morning!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:26.64,0:23:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time, on One Piece:
Dialogue: 10,0:23:27.72,0:23:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Dreams Don't Come True?! \NBellamy versus the Saruyama Alliance
Dialogue: 10,0:23:30.97,0:23:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna be the Pirate King!!
